msgctxt "1135"
msgid ""
"A Yamazaki whisky made with carefully selected, mature malts for a "
"flavorful, smooth finish."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1228"
msgid ""
"This is one of Japan's top single malt whiskies. It's become such a status "
"symbol that whisky aficionados the world over have heard of it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1367"
msgid ""
"They use carefully selected, perfectly matured single malts to get that "
"great, smooth flavor. It's popular overseas, too."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1489"
msgid ""
"A whisky made in the Southern Alps of Japan. Has a fruity flavor with smoky "
"accents."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1574"
msgid ""
"This one's made at Suntory's Hakushu distillery in Japan's South Alps, an "
"area famous for its mountain spring water."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1691"
msgid ""
"Its fruity, creamy flavor combined with a distinctly smoky accent makes for "
"a superb drinking experience."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1797"
msgid ""
"I recommend taking the first drink straight up, to fully appreciate its "
"quality."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1878"
msgid "One of Japan's premium brands, known internationally for its mellow flavor."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1954"
msgid ""
"This is a premium Japanese whisky that has won over whisky lovers around "
"the world."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2038"
msgid ""
"This whisky starts with a single malt aged in Japanese Mizunara oak and "
"then blended with over thirty different, painstakingly selected single "
"malts."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2188"
msgid ""
"The mellow flavor produced by this process has earned it a gold prize in an "
"international competition. The finish is particularly good."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2324"
msgid "A malt whisky good for experts and first-timers alike."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2379"
msgid ""
"The Hokuto is the result of extensive research into developing an easy to "
"drink malt whisky. It really reins in whisky's powerful taste, making it "
"good for first-timers."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2549"
msgid ""
"I think people who usually drink shochu will enjoy this whisky. The bamboo "
"charcoal filtration gives it a clean, pure taste."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2674"
msgid ""
"It's especially good mixed with an equal part of water or soda on the "
"rocks. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2752"
msgid ""
"The father of Japanese whisky, and possibly the most popular whisky in all "
"of Japan."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2837"
msgid ""
"Kakubin is probably the most popular whisky in Japan, wouldn't you agree? "
"Some call it the father of Japanese whisky.  "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2957"
msgid ""
"Its popularity shows no signs of waning, even after seventy years on the "
"market. It has a sweet aroma, depth, and full body. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3083"
msgid "The name Kakubin comes from its unique squared bottle shape."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3144"
msgid "A carefully distilled spirit with a bright aroma and sweet fullness."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3213"
msgid ""
"Another extremely popular Japanese whisky. Malt whisky aged in sherry "
"barrels at the Yamazaki Distillery are blended with carefully selected malt "
"and grain whiskies."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3379"
msgid ""
"It has a bright aroma and delivers a sweet fullness in the mouth, and the "
"finish is deep and mellow."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3480"
msgid ""
"A lot of people call it Daruma, because the round shape of its bottle looks "
"like a Daruma doll. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3577"
msgid "Standard Ballantine's scotch. Not too heavy, not too light, but just right."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3653"
msgid ""
"That's a standard scotch, made from a blend of over forty varieties of "
"single malts. Not too heavy, not too light. It's got a great balance to it. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3801"
msgid ""
"And the price isn't too high, either. I recommend it to casual scotch "
"drinkers. It's also a nice intro to blended whisky, if you've never tried "
"one before."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3957"
msgid "A silky bourbon with a sharp, clean finish."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4001"
msgid ""
"People have enjoyed this bourbon since the day it first came out in 1860. "
"It's the quintessential bourbon. The flavor is very American.   "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4140"
msgid ""
"Silky and smooth on the tongue, with a clean finish. This whiskey's "
"reasonable price also makes it a wonderful choice for a casual drink.  "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4280"
msgid "One of Japan's top brandies, famous for its fruity aroma and smooth flavor."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4356"
msgid ""
"That's one of Japan's premium brandies. This bestseller has won over "
"countless people with its bright, fruity bouquet and smooth taste."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4492"
msgid ""
"As for the name... V.S.O.P stands for Very Superior Old Pale. But you "
"probably already knew that.  "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4592"
msgid "A fruity brandy that's incredibly easy to drink."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4641"
msgid ""
"This is a well-priced brandy you can drink every day and still not get "
"tired of. It's characterized by crisp fruit flavors that come from the "
"freshest grapes."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4800"
msgid ""
"It has a crisp finish that makes it quite easy to drink. You can drink it "
"straight or use it in all sorts of cocktails.  "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4922"
msgid ""
"A stellar shochu made with top-grade sweet potatoes from southern Kagoshima "
"prefecture. Has a rounded body and a fruity fragrance."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5053"
msgid ""
"The Kuromaru is an exquisite blend of two types of shochu, one rich and "
"strong and the other light and full of fruit aromas."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5178"
msgid ""
"A unique variety of sweet potato from the Kagoshima region gives it a mild "
"flavor and refreshing, clean finish."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5290"
msgid "A premium Japanese beer made with only the finest malts."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5347"
msgid ""
"This beer won Japan's first gold award in an international competition and "
"then defended the title for the next two years. It's a premium beer by "
"Japanese and world standards."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5523"
msgid ""
"Unyielding commitment to quality ingredients and Suntory's years of brewing "
"know-how produce a delicious, almost magical flavor. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5653"
msgid ""
"A frosty glass of this beer while nibbling sashimi or enjoying a Blu-ray "
"movie on your day off... Now that's what I call living."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5782"
msgid "A clean spring water soju made with premier Korean barley."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5841"
msgid ""
"A prime example of Korean soju. A natural spring water base gives it a "
"clean taste, while premium Korean barley gives it a mellow, rounded flavor."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5988"
msgid ""
"It's not all that expensive, either. I'd say it offers excellent value for "
"the price. I used to drink this all the time, and its taste is still as "
"familiar as an old friend. "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6163"
msgid "To me, this bottle of soju brings back a lot of fond memories.  "
msgstr ""